        "is_strict_compatibility_enabled": true,
        "license": null,
        "release_notes": {
            "en-US": "New features:\n- Progress bar indicating zipping progress. \n- Zip only selected attachments.\n- Zip with password (currently unicode passwords are not supported).\n- Choose compression ratio.\n- Specify zip comment (currently unicode comments are not supported).\n- Rename attachments.\n- Zip grouping: zip all attachments to the same file, zip each attachment to a separate file, zip attachments with the same extension to the same file.\n\n- SmartZip: \n1. Skip files with a specific extension. \n2. Skip files smaller than a specific size.\n3. Skip attachments which the benefit from zipping them would be less than a specified percent. \nNote: This would take time as if the file was actually zipped.\n- Zip report of skipped files in the tooltip of the status bar.\n- Option to Use smartZip with autoZip.\n- Option for zip confirmation dialog when Autozipping.\n- Option for a password dialog for each file zipped. This allows having different passwords for each file in the zip.\n\n- Context menu in the attachments basket - allows quick access.\n- Redesign options dialog.\n- Improved localization support.\n- Support for thunderbird 2.0 beta 2\n\nBug Fixes:\n- Fixed bug in the zip structure which caused wrong timestamp of the zipped files.\n- Fixed bug in the zip structure which prevented deleting files from the zipped file.\n- Fixed bug in the zip structure which caused gmail to discard attachments zipped with the extension.\n- Fixed bug which caused zipping of forward attachments to have wrong names. This also caused a conflict with Enigmail extension.\n"
        },
        "reviewed": null,
        "url": "https://addons.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/addon/auto-zip-attachments/versions/0.5.1",
